The paper deals with the analysis of bit-wise demodulators for M-ary PAM over the AWGN channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The study of bit patterns and labelings also involves the analysis of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.SI). Finally, the numerical results and analysis of practical interest suggest a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
